Haze Node - Public Devnet Build ({{TAG}})
==========================================

THIS IS DEVNET. NOT MAINNET. HAZE HAS NO VALUE.
The chain may be reset (wiped back to block 0) at any time, without notice.
Nothing you do here - balances, stakes, names, minted assets - is guaranteed
to survive. Do not treat any HAZE balance as real or valuable.


RUNNING THE NODE
-----------------
From a terminal, in the folder you extracted this archive into:

    Windows:        haze.exe node
    macOS / Linux:  ./haze node

This starts a node listening for peer connections on 127.0.0.1:8333 and
serving a local HTTP API on 127.0.0.1:8332. By default it starts a fresh
chain from genesis and runs standalone (no known public peer to connect to
right now - see "CONNECTING TO OTHER PEERS" below).

Useful flags:
    --rpc-port <port>     change the local HTTP API port (default 8332)
    --bind <addr:port>    change the P2P listen address (default 127.0.0.1:8333)
    --peers <addr,addr>   comma-separated list of peer addresses to connect to
    --stake-key <key>     see "ABOUT VALIDATOR STAKING" below

Run `haze --help` (or `haze node --help`) for the full list.


WHERE YOUR DATA IS STORED
--------------------------
The node stores its chain database under the HAZE_DATA_DIR environment
variable if set, otherwise in a `haze_data` folder created next to wherever
you run the binary from. Deleting this folder resets your local node back
to genesis - it does not affect anyone else's node.


CHECKING SYNC STATUS
----------------------
While the node is running, in another terminal:

    curl http://127.0.0.1:8332/v1/status

This returns your node's current chain height, tip hash, number of active
validators, and mempool size. There's currently no public seed node to sync
against (see below), so on a freshly started node this height will just
reflect blocks your own node has produced, if any.


CONNECTING TO OTHER PEERS
---------------------------
A public seed node for this devnet isn't reachable yet - the hosted devnet
node's peer-to-peer port isn't currently exposed to the internet. Until
that's available, this binary is useful for running a fully standalone
local devnet (e.g. to test the wallet or explore the API) or for connecting
to another node's address directly via --peers, if someone gives you one.
Check https://github.com/Pranav00x/haze for updates on public peer
availability.


ABOUT VALIDATOR STAKING
--------------------------
Registering a UTXO as a validator stake (via the `stake` wallet command)
does not mean your node will propose blocks. It just publishes that
output's commitment on-chain, proving ownership by revealing its blinding
factor. To actually propose blocks with it, you separately need to run a
node with `--stake-key <that output's private key>` - registering and
proposing are two different steps.


VERIFYING YOUR DOWNLOAD
--------------------------
Each release archive ships with a matching .sha256 file. To verify:

    macOS / Linux:  shasum -a 256 -c haze-devnet-*.tar.gz.sha256
    Windows:        certutil -hashfile haze-devnet-*.zip SHA256
                    (compare the output against the .sha256 file by hand)


